               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Sǝmʿon näbiy “Vita of Simeon the Prophet” (fols. 2ra-30rb) 
                     II) Taʾammǝra Sǝmʿon näbiy “Miracle of Simeon the Prophet: 28 miracles (fols.
                     30rb-55rb)
 III) Qāl kidan, Covenant of Simeon the Prophet (fols.
                     55va-57rb)</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- Simeon the Prophet feaures in some Ethiopic texts, like the Synaxarion
                        with the commemorative notice dedicated to him for 8 Yakkātit (s. ColSyn X,
                        58-61), in the Gadla Samāʿtāt, the homily for 8 Yakkātit (s. EMML V, 345) or
                        in the 4th and 5th Miracles of Jesus (s. GrébMJ I, 603-07), but no text
                        comparable to Texts I-III have been identified so far, neither in Ethiopian
                        published sources nor in CANT.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
